If you have ordered</a></h3>
          <h4 class="meta">
    	<strong>Parka</strong><br/>
	  <abbr title="Saturday, December 12, 2009 - 11:14">December 12, 2009</abbr>, <br/>
	  <span class="time-ago">1 year 1 week ago</span><br />
	  <span class="comment-id">Comment id: 1027</span>
	</h4>
        <div class="comment-content ">
      <p>@kelvin<br />
If you have ordered any book from third party merchants, then your order will not go through because they normally don't ship to Singapore. </p>
<p>You must get it directly from Amazon. Under the price you must see the text </p>
<ul>
<li>In Stock. Ships from and sold by Amazon.com.</li>
<li>In Stock. Sold by ______(third party merchant name) and Fulfilled by Amazon</li>
</ul>
<p>If you're getting anything other than books or discs (excluding software), they don't ship to Singapore.</p>
<p>Anyway, during one of the steps on your checkout page, they will tell you specifically which item doesn't ship to Singapore.</p>
    </div> <!-- /comment content -->
          <div class="links">
        <ul class="links"><li class="comment_reply first last"><a href="/comment/reply/1136/1027">reply</a></li>
